column1: Protected area, by region, protected area, time  and  contents
Some areas are located in more than one county. Thus the sum of the

number in the counties is higher than the total number.
From
31.12.2003 onwards the area figures are calculated based on digital

overlay analysis, and a higher accuracy is obtained.
SSB has in
2013 change the projection WGS_1984_UTM_33N til ETRS_1989_LAEA. The

statistics areas may be a bit adjusted from earlier year
'Other
protections' include flora and fauna protection areas (biotop
protections), and since 2006 nature relics with an area protection
and biotops protected by the Wildlife Act are also included. <br
/>The numbers do not include flora- or fauna protections without area

protection.
Areas on Svalbard are protected according to the
Svalbard law. From 2009 are these areas included  in the total
numbers for protected areas. Figures per 31rst of December each year.
